1. Start the mininet topology by running bigtopo.py using below command:
	sudo mn --custom ~/bigtopo.py --topo mytopo --controller remote

2. Start RYU controller using below command:
	ryu-manager /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/ryu/app/simple_switch_13.py

3. Turn on Promiscuous mode, on the interfaces connected to HOST3 by running below commands:
	sudo ip link set s1-eth3 promisc on
	sudo ip link set s2-eth3 promisc on

4. Mirror traffic generated by HOST1, HOST2, HOST4, HOST5 on HOST3 by running below commands:
	sudo ovs-vsctl -- set Bridge s1 mirrors=@m -- --id=@s1-eth1 get Port s1-eth1 -- --id=@s1-eth2 get Port s1-eth2 -- --id=@s1-eth3 get Port s1-eth3 -- --id=@m 	create Mirror name=mymirror select-dst-port=@s1-eth1,@s1-eth2 select-src-port=@s1-eth1,@s1-eth2 output-port=@s1-eth3

	sudo ovs-vsctl -- set Bridge s2 mirrors=@m -- --id=@s2-eth1 get Port s2-eth1 -- --id=@s2-eth2 get Port s2-eth2 -- --id=@s2-eth3 get Port s2-eth3 -- --id=@m 	create Mirror name=mymirror select-dst-port=@s2-eth1,@s2-eth2 select-src-port=@s2-eth1,@s2-eth2 output-port=@s2-eth3

5. Use ITGRecv command on HOST1 to start listening to D-ITG traffic using below commands:
	xterm h1
	cd ditg/bin
	./ITGRecv

6. Use ITGSend command on HOST2 to generate traffic to HOST1 using below commands:
	xterm h2
	cd ditg/bin
	./ITGSend -a 10.0.0.1 -t 20000 -rp 9501 -u 500 1000 -B U 500 1000 U 500 1000

7. Run packet sniff program on HOST3 by running sniff.py using below commands:
	xterm h3
	sudo python3 sniff.py

8. Terminate sniff.py when no packets are being received, to see the graph plot of traffic captured and the samples captured.

9. Run samplingfreq.py to get the sampling frequency of last 'x' seconds.

===========================================================================

NOTES: 

1. bucket.txt contains original packet buckets, each containing packets in 1 second.
2. sampletimes.txt contains timestamps at which a sample is taken.

===========================================================================
